Interactive DAEMON-SNIFFER
Programs that intercept the network traffic flowing in and out of a system through network interfaces.
It has three main parts:
As interactive: there is command line interface which controls daemon execution;
As sniffer: Program that intercept the network traffic flowing in and out of a system through network interfaces;
As daemon: It works in background mode.


How to run daemon:
1)Must be a superuser:
sudo su
2)compile using gcc:
gcc -o main main.c shell.c binaryTree.c
3)run main:
./main

or

run runme.sh:
1):
bash runme.sh
2):
chmod u+x runme.sh
./runme.sh

Enjoy!

